<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,391]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,367,259,284]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">COMMENTS</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[383,459,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Ripersia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rehi">
<emphasis box="[383,400,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[416,459,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">rehi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from many grass species, and it is often a serious pest on rice in 
<collectingCountry box="[1334,1432,260,284]" name="Pakistan" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,209,295,319]" name="India" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[265,395,295,319]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
(Williams, 
<number box="[529,590,295,319]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2004.0">2004</number>
). This species was reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[971,1016,296,319]" name="Iran" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Iran</collectingCountry>
by Asadeh &amp; Mosadegh (
<number box="[1315,1375,295,319]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1991.0">1991</number>
), and since then it has been considered as a pest on sorghum and rice in the south of 
<collectingCountry box="[1029,1078,333,356]" name="Iran" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Due to this damage in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,199,368,391]" name="Iran" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Iran</collectingCountry>
, a study of its life history under Iranian conditions should be done.
</paragraph>
